Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Place the @Demi Garlic Baguettes{2} onto #baking tray{}. Bake on the middle shelf,
~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #saucepan on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams} and @King Prawns{150%grams} for
~{2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Reduce the heat to medium. Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams},
@Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Jus Paste{22%grams},
@Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{250%milliliter(s)}.

Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer.

Stir in the @Fresh Tagliatelle{200%grams}. Simmer, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so the prawns are pink outside and opaque inside.

Next, stir in half the @Parmigiano Reggiano{40%grams}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the tagliatelle between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Slice and serve the garlic baguettes alongside.

Enjoy!